#### Documenting after each video tutorial and implementation ####

Steps followed on Getting started with django project:

Step 1 : created and activated venv in /26_python_web/
>> python -m venv venv
>> venv/Scripts/activate

Step 2 : Installed django and verify version and other packages
>> pip install django
>> pip freeze
    asgiref==3.9.1
    Django==5.2.5
    sqlparse==0.5.3
    typing_extensions==4.14.1
    tzdata==2025.2
>> python -m django --verison
    5.2.5

Step 3 : Checkout the available django commands
>> python -m django
    Type 'python -m django help <subcommand>' for help on a specific subcommand.

Available subcommands:

[django]
    check
    compilemessages
    createcachetable
    dbshell
    diffsettings
    dumpdata
    flush
    inspectdb
    loaddata
    makemessages
    makemigrations
    migrate
    optimizemigration
    runserver
    sendtestemail
    shell
    sqlflush
    sqlmigrate
    sqlsequencereset
    squashmigrations
    startapp
    startproject
    test
    testserver

Step 4 : Create a new project
>> python -m django startproject django_project
    ** This will create folder "django_project" containing manage.py and other dafault files and folders **
    C:./26_python_for_web/django_project/
    │---db.sqlite3
    │---getting_started
    │---manage.py
    │
    └───django_project
        │---asgi.py
        │---settings.py
        │---urls.py
        │---wsgi.py
        │---__init__.py
        │
        └───__pycache__
                ...


Step 5 : Goto "django_project/" and run server
django_project/
 >> python manage.py runserver
    August 12, 2025 - 10:55:53
    Django version 5.2.5, using settings 'django_project.settings'Starting development server at http://127.0.0.1:8000/
    Quit the server with CTRL-BREAK.
        ** Open the given url http://127.0.0.1:8000/ in browser **

Step 6 : Explore the webpage
    ** given host is localhost: 127.0.0.1, Hence can change to http://localhost:8000/ **
    ** Try localhost:8000/admin >> will open django authentication site as give in file "./django_project/urls.py" **